title: Car rental in the U.S. - total cars in service 2002 to 2012
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Cars in service in thousands. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
In general Cars in service in thousands has rose over the Year.

Cars in service in thousands is roughly constant from 2002 to 2003, slightly increasing from 2003 to 2007, slightly decreasing from 2007 to 2009, roughly constant from 2009 to 2010, and finally slightly increasing from 2010 to 2012.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Cars in service in thousands, about 1861.0 was reported at Year 2007
Minimum Cars in service in thousands about 1617.0 was reached at Year 2003
